@context: Rahul Shetty Academy Practice Page
@title: complex_ui_inspector

# 🐾 RAHUL SHETTY HUNT: The Real Inspector Challenge
# Validation of radio buttons, autocomplete, tables, and hovers.
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FEATURES DEMONSTRATED:
#
#   VERIFY ... is checked / is not checked
#                       — Verifies the checked state of checkboxes and
#                         radio buttons. "is not checked" confirms the
#                         element was unchecked (e.g. after a toggle).
#
#   VERIFY ... is NOT present
#                       — Negative assertion. Confirms that the target
#                         text is NOT visible on the page. Useful for
#                         hide/show tests and confirming deletions.
#
#   HOVER over 'Target' — Triggers a mouse hover on the resolved element.
#                         Useful for testing tooltip menus, dropdowns that
#                         appear on hover, and hover-state CSS changes.
#
#   EXTRACT ... into {var}
#                       — Captures table cell text based on row context.
#                         Multiple extractions build up a variable store
#                         that can be referenced in subsequent steps.
#
#   Autocomplete        — Fill a partial value, then Click on the
#                         suggestion that appears. The engine resolves
#                         the suggestion list item via standard heuristics.
#
#   Toggle checkbox     — Click a checkbox, verify checked; click again,
#                         verify not checked. Demonstrates the engine's
#                         ability to track state changes.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: Navigate to practice page
    NAVIGATE to https://rahulshettyacademy.com/AutomationPractice/

STEP 2: Radio buttons
    # "radio button for" triggers strict radio-mode scoring.
    CLICK the radio button for 'Radio1'
    VERIFY that 'Radio1' is checked
    CLICK the radio button for 'Radio3'
    VERIFY that 'Radio3' is checked

STEP 3: Autocomplete field
    # Type partial text, then click the matching suggestion.
    FILL 'Suggession Class' field with 'Ukra'
    CLICK the 'Ukraine' element
    VERIFY that 'Ukraine' is present

STEP 4: Dropdown
    # Sequential dropdown selections on the same <select> element.
    SELECT 'Option1' from the 'Dropdown' dropdown
    SELECT 'Option2' from the 'Dropdown' dropdown
    SELECT 'Option3' from the 'Dropdown' dropdown

STEP 5: Checkboxes
    # Toggle pattern: check → verify checked → uncheck → verify not checked.
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Option1'
    VERIFY that 'Option1' is checked
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Option2'
    VERIFY that 'Option2' is checked
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Option3'
    VERIFY that 'Option3' is checked
    UNCHECK the checkbox for 'Option1'
    VERIFY that 'Option1' is NOT checked

STEP 6: Name field and alert
    FILL 'Enter Your Name' field with 'Cyber Manul'
    VERIFY that 'Cyber Manul' is present
    # The Confirm button triggers a browser alert that clears the field.
    CLICK the 'Confirm' button
    # Negative assertion: the text should no longer be visible.
    VERIFY that 'Cyber Manul' is NOT present

STEP 7: Scroll and extract prices
    SCROLL DOWN
    # EXTRACT captures table data into runtime variables.
    EXTRACT the 'Price of Selenium' into {selenium_price}
    EXTRACT the 'Price of Appium' into {appium_price}
    EXTRACT the 'Price of Learn SQL' into {sql_price}
    VERIFY that '25' is present

STEP 8: Hide / Show element
    FILL 'Hide/Show Example' field with 'Ghost Mode'
    VERIFY that 'Ghost Mode' is present
    CLICK the 'Hide' button
    # After hiding, the text should NOT be present.
    VERIFY that 'Ghost Mode' is NOT present
    CLICK the 'Show' button
    VERIFY that 'Ghost Mode' is present

STEP 9: Dynamic table extraction
    SCROLL DOWN
    EXTRACT the 'Amount of Jack' into {jack_amount}
    EXTRACT the 'Amount of Joe' into {joe_amount}
    VERIFY that 'Joe' is present

STEP 10: Mouse hover
    # HOVER triggers Playwright's hover() on the resolved element.
    # The hidden menu items become visible after the hover action.
    HOVER over the 'Mouse Hover' button
    VERIFY that 'Reload' is present
    VERIFY that 'Top' is present

STEP 11: Back to top
    CLICK on the 'Top' link
    VERIFY that 'Practice Page' is present
DONE.
